In research areas that are hazardous, our robots powered by artificial intelligence can replace humans, collect data efficiently (avoiding human error), and reduce human deaths.

In research areas that are not hazardous, our robots powered by artificial intelligence can collect data much faster, efficiently and present them to a logical fashion to humans.
Our robots can work 24/7 given power while still retaining the intelligence of a human 
Robots can store a mass amount of information and use it at a later time. The excellence in memory can help speed up experiments and research.
